    "skill": {
        "name": "Arcana",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "Arcana measures how much you know about arcane magic and creatures.\n* ***Recall Knowledge*** about arcane theories; magic traditions; creatures of arcane significance (like constructs, beasts, and elementals); and the Astral Plane, Elemental Planes, and the Netherworld.",
        "subtype": "skill",
        "key_ability": "int",
        "skill_type": "character_skill",
        "actions": [
            {
                "name": "Borrow an Arcane Spell",
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "text": "If you're an arcane spellcaster who prepares spells, you can attempt to prepare a spell from someone else's arcane spellbook, arcane witch familiar, or the like. The GM sets the DC for the check based on the spell's rank and rarity; it's typically a bit easier than Learning the Spell.",
                "sources": [
                    {
